size:
OMEGA’s Museum Collection reflects the noble heritage of a great brand. Outstanding timepieces are selected from the Museum – they have to be more than fifty years old – and are honoured with a reissue incorporating both traditional design excellence and OMEGA’s innovative contemporary watchmaking.





The OMEGA Museum Collection N° 6: “Tonneau Renversé” features a silver dial with 18K red gold applied hour indexes and a small seconds dial. The 35 x 35 mm 18K white and red gold case is presented on a black leather strap with an 18K white gold buckle. The caseback features a special Museum engraving and the limited edition number. This official certified chronometer is powered by OMEGA’s calibre 2202, a self-winding movement with a Co-Axial escapement. This watch was produced in an edition limited to 1952 pieces.

    Case diameter: 35 mm

What Makes This Model Special? 


This is among the most stunning & difficult to acquire Speedmaster variants in Omega’s lineup. With its sun-brushed green PVD dial, green ceramic bezel ring with Omega Ceragold tachymeter scale, and breathtaking Moonshine gold case, this timepiece commands attention while remaining classy. The Speedmaster has been a part of all six moon landings and is why this iconic line is dubbed the “Moonwatch.” This piece embodies the legacy and heritage Omega has been pioneering for over 60 years.

This model, with its scratch-resistant sapphire crystal, features a blue dial with a date window at the 6 o’clock position. The dial presents a small seconds sub-dial, as well as 60-minute and 12-hour counters on one dial for intuitive reading of elapsed time. The blue ceramic unidirectional rotating divers’ bezel, with its Liquidmetal diving scale, is mounted on a 45.5 mm titanium case and is presented on a titanium bracelet.





The OMEGA Seamaster Planet Ocean 600M is water resistant to 60 bar (600 metres / 2000 feet), and has a helium-escape valve. The OMEGA Co-Axial calibre 9300 at the heart of this certified chronometer timepiece can be seen through the transparent caseback.

size:
Oris Ocean Trilogy Set - a limited & numbered edition set of only 200 sets, with all 3 pieces sharing the same limited edition number. The trio of watches includes the: • Oris Blue Whale limited edition 200 pieces, available exclusively as part of the Oris Ocean Trilogy set).

• Oris Great Barrier Reef III limited edition 2000 pieces.

• Oris Clean Ocean limited edition 2000 pieces.

The set is delivered in an exclusive & eye-catching presentation box produced from used plastic bottles. Only chemically inert recycled plastic waste was selected as part of the process. The box is created in 4 steps: • Use plastic bottles are collected.

• The plastic bottles are then shredded into small pieces.

• The pieces are selectively hand arranged & then pressed into a panel. The hand selection & positioning of the various colored bottle makes each panel unique.

• Finally the panels are cut to size & assembled as the outer shell of the Oris Ocean Trilogy presentation box .

Oris Blue Whale 01 743 7734 4185-Set: • Case diameter: 45.50mm

• Case back: Special engraving with Blue Whale image.

• Crown: screw down.

• Bezel: Blue ceramic with diving scale.

• Dial: Gradient blue dial, applied hour markers with luminous fill, hands with luminous fill.

• Water resistance: 500m.

• Features: Chronograph function, small seconds sub-dial at 9 o'clock, date window at 4.30 o'clock.

• Movement: Oris caliber 771 (base SW 510), beats at 28,800 vph, contains 27 jewels & has a power reserve of +/- 48 hours.

• Water resistance: 300m.

Oris Clean Ocean 01 733 7732 4185-Set: • Case diameter: 39.50mm
